<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4544408>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Nephochaetopteryx affinis Lopes, 1936, male terminalia of holotype (MNRJ). A. Cercus and surstylus, left lateral view. B. Cerci, dorsal view (spines and setation omitted on the left side). C. Pregonite, left lateral view. D. Postgonite, left lateral view. E. Sternite 5, ventral view (setation omitted on the left side). F. Phallus, left lateral view.Abbreviations: bp = basiphallus; dp = distiphallus; ip = inner process of vesica; ls = lateral stylus; ms = median stylus; ve = vesica. Scale bars:A, B, E = 0.1 mm; C, D, F = 0.05 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4544408/files/figure.png" .

